{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Proteins in this entry form part of an accessory Sec system which is involved in the export of serine-rich glycoproteins important for virulence in a number of Gram-positive species, including Streptococcus gordonii and Staphylococcus aureus [[cite:PUB00053479], [cite:PUB00098563]]. Asp2 directly interacts with Aps1 and Asp3 to form a complex and stabilizes it; this complex is essential for substrate export. Asp2 and Asp3 interact directly with GspB and may function in part as chaperones in the early phase of GspB transport [[cite:PUB00067674]]. Moreover, Asp2 acetylates the GlcNAc residues on GspB. Asp1/2/3 complex stimulates the ATPase activity of SecA2 and also affects the export and glycosylation of pneumococcal serine-rich repeat proteins (PrsPs) [[cite:PUB00098563]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR03712" "accessory Sec system protein Asp2"}, "pfam" {"PF16929" "Accessory Sec system GspB-transporter"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Accessory Sec system protein Asp2", "short" "Asp2"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 2, "domain_architectures" 7, "proteomes" 121, "taxa" 786, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1012, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1011, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 784}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR022267", :literature {"PUB00067674" {"URL" nil, "issue" "13", "authors" ["Yen YT" "Seepersaud R" "Bensing BA" "Sullam PM."], "ISO_journal" "J. Bacteriol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1128/JB.00057-11", "medline_journal" "J Bacteriol", "title" "Asp2 and Asp3 interact directly with GspB, the export substrate of the Streptococcus gordonii accessory Sec System.", "year" 2011, "raw_pages" "3165-74", "volume" "193", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 21531800}, "PUB00053479" {"URL" ni